3 SECTION 2A.4.(d) Management of Funds. – All funds used for Hurricane Helene
4 recovery as set forth in this section shall be managed in a separate project account within the
5 Reserve for General Maintenance (GMR). Federal reimbursements for funds expended from this
6 account shall be deposited in this account. Upon recovery completion, any remaining Recovery
7 Funds shall be transferred to GMR for use by the Department.
8 SECTION 2A.4.(e) Cash Watch Weekly Report. – In addition to the other items
9 published in the weekly report required under G.S. 143C-6-11(n), the Department shall include
10 the total sum of Hurricane Helene expenditures and the total sum of federal reimbursements
11 received by the Department. This requirement shall remain in effect until recovery is complete
12 and the Department has received all federal reimbursements.
13 SECTION 2A.5.(a) North Carolina Railroad Dividend. – G.S. 124-18, as it existed
14 before it was repealed by Section 4.4(b) of S.L. 2019-231, is reenacted and reads as rewritten:
15 "§ 124-18. Dividends required of State-owned railroad company.
16 Any State-owned railroad company that has trackage in more than two counties shall issue
17 an annual cash dividend to the State. The dividend shall be deposited in the Freight Rail & Rail
18 Crossing Safety Improvement Fund (FRRCSI) within the Highway Fund. The amount of the
19 annual dividend is twenty-five percent (25%) of the company's income from the prior year's
20 trackage rights agreements. The dividend is due by February 15 of each year, and interest shall
21 accrue at the annual rate of prime plus one percent (1%) if the payment is not paid by the due
22 date. The Directors of any State-owned railroad company who vote for or assent to the dividend
23 required under this section shall not be held liable under G.S. 55-8-33."
24 SECTION 2A.5.(b) For the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium, the funds deposited in
25 accordance with G.S. 124-18, as enacted by subsection (a) of this section, are hereby appropriated
26 to the Department of Transportation as follows:
